Data.event_text: 1 January  The presidential decree on dissolving of Russian Federal Space Agency and transforming it into the Roscosmos Space Corporation has come into force.
1923 January  Junior 2016 Russian Figure Skating Championships in Chelyabinsk.
815 February  2016 St. Petersburg Ladies Trophy.

Data.event_text: 1620 February  2016 Russian Figure Skating Championships Final in Saransk, Mordovia.

2529 February  Vorkuta mine disaster Ignition of leaking methane gas caused a series of explosions that caused the deaths of 36 people, including 31 miners and five rescue workers, in a coal mine near the city of Vorkuta, Komi Republic, Russia.

14 March  Russian military intervention in the Syrian Civil War Putin announced that the mission which he set for the Russian military in Syria "has been accomplished" and he ordered the withdrawal of the "main part" of the Russian forces from Syria.

19 March  Flydubai Flight 981 with Boeing 737-800 made two unsuccessful landing attempts at Rostov-on-Don Airport in inclement weather. It reached an altitude of 4,000 feet (1,200 m) (during its second go-around), but then suddenly went down and crashed into the ground at a high speed. All 62 people on board the aircraft were killed in the crash.
5 April  Internal Troops became the newly formed National Guard of Russia. The Federal Migration Service and the Federal Drug Control Service of Russia were subordinated to MVD.
28 April  Vostochny Cosmodrome.

Data.event_text: 622 May  2016 IIHF World Championship.

17 August  Federal Security Service (FSB) officers kill at least four suspected North Caucasus Islamic militants during a counter-terrorism raid on an apartment building in the Russian city of Saint Petersburg.[citation needed]

27 August  A fire at a warehouse in Moscow, Russia, kills at least 17 people, all migrant workers from Kyrgyzstan.  The Investigative Committee of Russia, which reports directly to President Vladimir Putin, says a criminal inquiry has been launched.

links.text: -Nechepurenko, Ivan (27 August 2016). "Moscow Warehouse Fire Kills at Least 17 Migrant Workers". The New York Times – via NYTimes.com.-

Data.event_text: 3 October  President Putin suspends the 2000 nuclear pact with the United States on cleaning up weapons-grade plutonium.

links.text: -"Putin suspends nuclear pact, raising stakes in row with Washington". Reuters. 3 October 2016. Retrieved 24 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: 5 October  Vladimir Putin suspends the 2013 nuclear pact with the United States on uranium research.

links.text: -"Russia suspends nuclear agreement, ends uranium research pact with United States". Reuters. 5 October 2016. Retrieved 24 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: 9 October  Eight militants, who planned attacks in Chechnya, were killed in a shootout with police. Four officers were injured as well.[citation needed]
8 October  Russia deploys the nuclear-capable Iskander mobile short-range ballistic missile system to the Kaliningrad Oblast.

links.text: -"Russia deploys nuclear-capable missiles in Kaliningrad". BBC News. 8 October 2016. Retrieved 24 October 2016.-

Data.event_text: 23 October  A gas explosion in the Russian city of Ryazan kills at least 3 people and injures 13 others

links.text: -"3 dead in Russian apartment explosion". AP News. 23 October 2016. Retrieved 7 May 2024.-

Data.event_text: 24 October   The Tolmachevy Sisters Concert in Minsk airs live on TV Channels Worldwide, including Freeform in the United States, Urging Viewers to vote for Donald Trump.
6 November  Explosion killed 6 people in Ivanovo a city in Russia.

links.text: -"6 dead, 4 injured in Russian apartment explosion". AP News. 6 November 2016. Retrieved 7 May 2024.-

Data.event_text: 25 December  A Tupolev Tu-154 crashes near Sochi, Russia, killing all 92 people on board, including 64 members of the Alexandrov Ensemble.[citation needed]
